			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Ability: Mend Companion 
<br />
Cost: 5 AA points in the Class section 
<br />
Pre-req: requires 6 General and 12 Archtype AA points spent 
<br />
Description: This ability allows you to instantly cast a Lay on Hands type of spell on your pet. 
<br />
Reuse Timer: 36 minutes base, 27 minutes with Hastened Mending I (2 AA), 18 minutes with HM2 (2 AA), 9 minutes with HM3 (2 AA) 
<br />

<br />
Ability: Hasted Mend 
<br />
Cost: 2 AA points per level in the PoP Abilities section 
<br />
Pre-req: Mend Companion, level 61 for the first rank, level 63 for the second rank, level 65 for the third rank. 
<br />
Description: Decreases the reuse time of Mend Companion by 25% per rank, for a final reuse time of 9 minutes at level 3. 
<br />

<br />
This does (Level x 33 + 1) HP of direct healing to your pet. <span style="font-weight: bold">At level 65, it does 2146 HP instantly</span>.
<br />

<br />
Improved Healing focuses do not work on this AA. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The formula at Level 70 caps out at (70 X 33) + 1 = 2,311 HP healed.  
<br />

<br />
Now lets look at Pet HP values for Level 65 Rathe's Son and what it will heal now and at level 70.
<br />

<br />
Unfocused 
<br />
===Pet Level 60 
<br />
===Pet HP 4800 
<br />
===Mend heals 2146 now or 44%, at level 70 it will heal 2,311 or 48%
<br />
 
<br />
Summoner's Boon 
<br />
===Pet Level 61 
<br />
===Pet Hp 5300
<br />
===Mend heals 2146 now or 40%, at level 70 it will heal 2,311 or 43%
<br />

<br />
Minion of Darkness 
<br />
===Pet Level 62 
<br />
===Pet HP 5520
<br />
===Mend heals 2146 now or 38%, at level 70 it will heal 2,311 or 41%
<br />

<br />
Minion of Eternity 
<br />
===Pet Level 63 
<br />
===Pet HP 6240
<br />
===Mend heals 2146 now or 34%, at level 70 it will heal 2,311 or 37%
<br />

<br />
Ritual Summoning 
<br />
===Pet Level 64 
<br />
===Pet HP 6550
<br />
===Mend heals 2146 now or 32%, at level 70 it will heal 2,311 or 35%
<br />

<br />
Since the formula only scales with level (and thats most likely going to be fixed at 70 for at least one-two years based on prior history of increasing level cap) you can see that Mend Companion is nearing the 30% and lower range at the moment.
<br />

<br />
With OOW this will only be exacerbated as the new pets will have even more HP and the % healed will go down across the board.
<br />

<br />
This is one of our really great AA's and is useful to all mages regardless of playstyle raid, group or solo.  AS such would like to suggest this be looked at and made to scale instead of stagnate due to being capped based upon level of the caster.  
<br />

<br />
I propose capping the heal based on the pet's total HP.  A flat 50% heal of the pet's total HP.  This is in line with the current heal ratio on unfocused pets (48% on unfocused Rathe's Son at level 70) and allows the ability to scale over time as pets receive upgrades in future expansions.
<br />

<br />
Example would be:
<br />

<br />
Unfocused 
<br />
===Pet Level 60 
<br />
===Pet HP 4800 
<br />
NOW - Mend heals 2146 now or 44%, at level 70 it will heal 2,311 or 48%
<br />
PROPOSED - Mend would heal 2400 HP which is 50%
<br />

<br />
Ritual Summoning 
<br />
===Pet Level 64 
<br />
===Pet HP 6550
<br />
NOW - Mend heals 2146 now or 32%, at level 70 it will heal 2,311 or 35%
<br />
PROPOSED - Mend would heal 3225 HP which is 50%
<br />

<br />
This allows the ability to scale with the caster as he/she gains power through focus items and expansions with stronger pets.
<br />

<br />
Any suggestions/comments?<br />_________________<br /><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" align="left"><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26797"><img src="http://www.jtbates.net/everquest/images/jtshieldtransparent.gif" border="0" /></a></td><td><a href="http://www.fohguild.org">[Fires of Heaven]</a> - <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=3239">[Magician's Tower Library]</a></td></tr><tr><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold">Join us in serverwide.magicians:fluffy</span></span></tr></table><br>
<br />
<br></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Jaytee Bushwacker on Mon Aug 09, 2004 4:08 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
