				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My Rathe's Son with Ritual Summoning has an obscene amount of HP
<br />

<br />
6550 Base
<br />
655 with Elemental Durability 3
<br />
600 from pet toys
<br />
2402 from full raid buffs
<br />
----
<br />
10,207 HP total
<br />

<br />
Mend Companion, doing 2146, does a mere 21% to its HP total.
<br />

<br />
I'd <span style="font-style: italic">guesstimate </span>a base Child of Earth pet (level 70 earth) will have about 6000 HP, and guesstimate a Ritual Summoning Child of Earth will have 8000 HP base (I don't know anything about the Omens pets, btw). Throw in toys and full Omens buffs and we're talking 12,522. A level 70 mend will only do an 18.5% heal.
<br />

<br />
As it stands, mend companion will be virtually worthless in Omens unless its upgraded.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Xalmat Lunaire</a> - <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Magician's Tower</a> - <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewforum.php?f=9" target="_blank" class="postlink">Lead Librarian</a>
